Female genitalia (
Fig. 37
). Papillae anales rectangular, setose. Apophyses posteriores about three times length of apophysis anteriores. Eighth tergum with anterior margin protruded rhombically, heavily sclerotized. Seventh tergum and sternum weakly sclerotized posteriorly, with dense microtrichia on lateral sides of distal half, concave on posterior margin. Lamella antevaginalis heavily sclerotized, trapezoidal. Ductus bursae membranous, with dense minute denticles on inner surface, about 1.2 times length of corpus bursae. Ductus seminalis arising from posterior 1 / 3 of ductus bursae, dilated distally. Corpus bursae ovate, with scattered minute granules on inner surface except two rounded areas bearing dense minute denticles.
